WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.360
If you've got a Bible with you,

2
00:00:01.360 --> 00:00:04.520
do please turn with me to Ephesians chapter one,

3
00:00:04.520 --> 00:00:07.240
or it's also there in your worship guide.

4
00:00:07.240 --> 00:00:08.840
If you need that, there on the back.

5
00:00:08.840 --> 00:00:11.400
Ephesians chapter one.

6
00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:13.920
Last week we looked at this same passage

7
00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:15.160
that we're looking at this morning,

8
00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:17.000
and we focused on the spiritual blessings

9
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:18.880
that are ours in Christ.

10
00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:22.320
We looked at adoption, election, redemption,

11
00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:23.840
our inheritance.

12
00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:27.640
But scripture's like a multifaceted diamond, right?

13
00:00:27.640 --> 00:00:29.800
You can take the same passage

14
00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:31.600
and turn it in a different direction

15
00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:35.800
and see God's glory refracted in a different way.

16
00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:38.280
So what I want us to do is look at the same passage

17
00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:41.000
we looked at last week, but from a different angle.

18
00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.200
And so last week we looked at the blessings,

19
00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:45.320
and this week I really want us to see the God

20
00:00:45.320 --> 00:00:48.720
who blesses us from this passage.

21
00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:50.400
Now so let's read Ephesians chapter one,

22
00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:52.520
verses three to 14 together.

23
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:56.040
It says, blessed be the God and father

24
00:00:56.040 --> 00:00:58.320
of our Lord Jesus Christ,

25
00:00:58.360 --> 00:01:00.040
who has blessed us in Christ

26
00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:03.600
with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly places,

27
00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:05.360
even as he chose us in him

28
00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:07.720
before the foundation of the world,

29
00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:11.160
that we should be holy and blameless before him.

30
00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:14.640
In love he predestined us for adoption to himself

31
00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:17.400
as sons through Jesus Christ,

32
00:01:17.400 --> 00:01:19.960
according to the purpose of his will,

33
00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:22.320
to the praise of his glorious grace,

34
00:01:22.320 --> 00:01:25.040
with which he has blessed us in the beloved.

35
00:01:25.040 --> 00:01:27.920
In him we have redemption through his blood,

36
00:01:27.920 --> 00:01:30.240
the forgiveness of our trespasses,

37
00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:32.120
according to the riches of his grace,

38
00:01:32.120 --> 00:01:36.040
which he lavished upon us in all wisdom and insight,

39
00:01:36.040 --> 00:01:39.080
making known to us the mystery of his will,

40
00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:42.000
according to his purpose, which he set forth in Christ

41
00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:44.360
as a plan for the fullness of time

42
00:01:44.360 --> 00:01:46.480
to unite all things in him,

43
00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:49.400
things in heaven and things on earth.

44
00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:52.000
In him we have obtained an inheritance,

45
00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:54.720
having been predestined according to the purpose of him

46
00:01:54.720 --> 00:01:58.560
who works all things according to the counsel of his will,

47
00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:01.200
so that we who were the first to hope in Christ

48
00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:03.480
might be to the praise of his glory.

49
00:02:03.480 --> 00:02:07.260
In him you also, when you heard the word of truth,

50
00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:10.600
the gospel of your salvation and believed in him

51
00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:13.080
were sealed with the promised Holy Spirit,

52
00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:15.440
who was the guarantee of our inheritance

53
00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:17.680
until we acquire possession of it

54
00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:20.560
to the praise of his glory.

55
00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:21.880
This is the word of the Lord.

56
00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:24.440
Let's pray.

57
00:02:25.160 --> 00:02:30.080
The grass withers and the flowers fade,

58
00:02:31.080 --> 00:02:34.680
but your word, oh Lord, stands forever.

59
00:02:34.680 --> 00:02:36.920
So Father, as we open your word together,

60
00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:40.520
I pray that you would plant it deeply in our hearts

61
00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:43.520
and that you would cause it to bear fruit for your glory

62
00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:45.240
in Jesus' name, amen.

63
00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:50.440
Just as we get started, I'm gonna ask you a dangerous question.

64
00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:52.960
What is the worst sermon you've ever heard?

65
00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:54.720
And please don't say last week.

66
00:02:56.680 --> 00:02:58.520
I've heard some pretty bad ones in my life.

67
00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:01.440
I remember one was focused,

68
00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:03.880
the whole thing was about UFOs, I kid you not.

69
00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:08.840
Another one was a list of signs that you are only

70
00:03:08.840 --> 00:03:11.600
pretending to be King James only.

71
00:03:11.600 --> 00:03:13.080
In other words, that you only use

72
00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:15.160
the King James version of the Bible.

73
00:03:15.160 --> 00:03:17.240
And it was that, you say you only use that version,

74
00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:20.160
but here's seven reasons why I know you're lying,

75
00:03:20.160 --> 00:03:23.320
that you really would read other versions of the Bible.

76
00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:24.200
A real sermon.

77
00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:28.800
But perhaps the most recent sermon I've heard

78
00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:32.160
that would maybe be on the list was at a dinner

79
00:03:32.160 --> 00:03:35.000
that I went to and there was a speaker afterwards.

80
00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.680
And they got up and they began their talk with a skit.

81
00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:40.600
And so they actually went out into the crowd

82
00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:43.320
and they passed out the script for the skit

83
00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:45.640
and the microphone got passed around.

84
00:03:45.640 --> 00:03:48.800
And the skit was a way of explaining the gospel.

85
00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:50.600
And the skit started off with somebody

86
00:03:50.600 --> 00:03:52.280
who was God the Father.

87
00:03:52.280 --> 00:03:55.760
And God the Father was really, really angry.

88
00:03:55.760 --> 00:04:00.040
He was furious at all of humanity, like all of us.

89
00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:01.280
He's mad.

90
00:04:02.360 --> 00:04:05.320
And he is going to punish us.

91
00:04:05.320 --> 00:04:10.240
But then, person number two steps in, God the Son.

92
00:04:10.240 --> 00:04:13.600
And he's saying, Dad, please no, don't punish them.

93
00:04:13.600 --> 00:04:15.920
I love them.

94
00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:20.040
And I want to go and give myself and die in their place.

95
00:04:20.040 --> 00:04:21.680
And the Father was not having it.

96
00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:25.760
And they argued back and forth about this in this play.

97
00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:28.840
And then it got so bad that they needed a mediator

98
00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:30.280
to step in.

99
00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:34.360
And you guessed it sadly, in walks the Holy Spirit

100
00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:35.880
who then functioned as a mediator

101
00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:38.260
between God the Father and God the Son

102
00:04:38.260 --> 00:04:39.760
so that they could come to an agreement

103
00:04:39.760 --> 00:04:42.400
that yes, he would allow the Son to come

104
00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:44.640
and die for us.

105
00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:48.720
It was cringe worthy to say the least.

106
00:04:48.720 --> 00:04:50.560
The angry Father, the benevolent Son

107
00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:52.160
and the peacemaking Spirit.

108
00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:56.640
But at least within the explanation maybe,

109
00:04:56.640 --> 00:04:59.240
there's pointing us to the fact that yes,

110
00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:02.400
God is a Trinity, Father, Son and Holy Spirit

111
00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:03.660
in this one God.

112
00:05:03.660 --> 00:05:06.260
But that isn't enough to just say

113
00:05:06.260 --> 00:05:08.760
God is Father, Son and Spirit.

114
00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:11.800
You know, at best maybe it tells us

115
00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:15.920
that we should praise Jesus for having died for us.

116
00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:22.520
But it leaves us with a questionable view of the Father.

117
00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:26.280
And not really knowing who the Holy Spirit is at all.

118
00:05:26.280 --> 00:05:27.880
But our text this morning,

119
00:05:27.880 --> 00:05:29.760
from the angle we're gonna see it from,

120
00:05:29.760 --> 00:05:33.000
shows us all three of the persons of the Trinity

121
00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:38.000
working together in perfect harmony to save us.

122
00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:40.040
This is the God that we praise.

123
00:05:42.480 --> 00:05:45.600
Verse three, blessed be the God and Father

124
00:05:45.600 --> 00:05:48.440
of our Lord Jesus Christ who has blessed us

125
00:05:48.440 --> 00:05:51.640
with every spiritual blessing in Christ Jesus.

126
00:05:51.640 --> 00:05:54.680
So right from the beginning of this long sentence

127
00:05:54.680 --> 00:05:57.920
where Paul is praising God, you see Father, Son and Spirit,

128
00:05:57.920 --> 00:05:59.720
we're blessed by the Father.

129
00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:03.800
He's the eternal loving Father of Jesus Christ, his Son.

130
00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:04.800
You see that there?

131
00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:07.240
We are blessed in Christ.

132
00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:09.600
So we're blessed in the Son.

133
00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:12.840
And we're blessed with every spiritual blessing.

134
00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:14.600
And of course, as we saw last week,

135
00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:18.160
that tells us about the nature of these blessings.

136
00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:20.220
But it also alludes to the fact

137
00:06:20.220 --> 00:06:23.920
that they are conveyed to us by the Holy Spirit.

138
00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:26.640
You see that develop as the chapter goes on.

139
00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:28.400
But here's the point, the persons of the Trinity

140
00:06:28.400 --> 00:06:32.680
do not work at odds with one another in our redemption.

141
00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:34.480
They work together in perfect harmony

142
00:06:34.480 --> 00:06:38.360
so we can sing as we do the doxology.

143
00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:43.400
Praise Father, Son and Holy Ghost.

144
00:06:44.280 --> 00:06:46.800
And this symphony of redemption occurs

145
00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:49.720
in three movements that we see here.

146
00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:52.040
And the three movements are the fact

147
00:06:52.040 --> 00:06:54.200
that it was planned by the Father

148
00:06:54.200 --> 00:06:57.480
and then secondly that it was accomplished by the Son.

149
00:06:57.480 --> 00:06:58.720
And then thirdly and lastly,

150
00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:02.640
we see that it was applied by the Spirit.

151
00:07:02.640 --> 00:07:04.520
Now we're gonna work through all three of those

152
00:07:04.520 --> 00:07:06.760
this morning, but just to forewarn you,

153
00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:09.000
we're gonna give more time to the first two

154
00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:10.160
and touch on the last one

155
00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:12.400
and then spend more time next week looking at that.

156
00:07:12.400 --> 00:07:15.480
So if we get two thirds of the way through

157
00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:17.640
and you're like, we've got another one,

158
00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:19.800
just know there's not gonna be much time there at the end.

159
00:07:19.800 --> 00:07:23.680
So first of all, our redemption is planned by the Father.

160
00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:25.960
These blessings that we've received in Christ

161
00:07:25.960 --> 00:07:28.880
have been given to us because of the Father's plan.

162
00:07:28.880 --> 00:07:33.520
So Paul repetitively in this section here

163
00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:36.800
draws our attention to God's sovereignty.

164
00:07:36.800 --> 00:07:40.880
He talks about God's will in verses five, nine and 11.

165
00:07:40.880 --> 00:07:43.160
He talks about God's purpose or his good pleasure

166
00:07:43.160 --> 00:07:45.000
in verses five and nine.

167
00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:46.920
In verse 10, he talks about God's plan.

168
00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:49.880
In verse 11, he talks about God's counsel.

169
00:07:49.880 --> 00:07:52.500
Last week we looked at the verbs that are there as well.

170
00:07:52.500 --> 00:07:56.560
So he talks about God choosing and predestining.

171
00:07:57.720 --> 00:07:59.200
But I wanna draw our attention particularly

172
00:07:59.200 --> 00:08:01.700
to verses nine and 10.

173
00:08:01.740 --> 00:08:04.740
So last week I mentioned this 202 word sentence.

174
00:08:04.740 --> 00:08:06.860
You know, Paul is just gushing with praise.

175
00:08:06.860 --> 00:08:09.940
A lot is happening, but he gets to the main point

176
00:08:09.940 --> 00:08:13.260
of what he's saying in verses nine and 10.

177
00:08:13.260 --> 00:08:17.140
Okay, these verses really summarize what he's saying here

178
00:08:17.140 --> 00:08:19.580
that's kind of pinnacle, but also they summarize

179
00:08:19.580 --> 00:08:21.780
the message of the entire book of Ephesians.

180
00:08:21.780 --> 00:08:23.820
So if you're wondering what this whole series is about,

181
00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:26.700
it's summarized in verses nine and 10.

182
00:08:26.700 --> 00:08:30.180
And there we see that God is making known to us

183
00:08:30.220 --> 00:08:34.660
the mystery of his will according to his purpose,

184
00:08:34.660 --> 00:08:37.340
which he set forth in Christ as a plan

185
00:08:37.340 --> 00:08:41.760
for the fullness of time to unite all things in him,

186
00:08:41.760 --> 00:08:45.900
things in heaven and things on earth.

187
00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:47.900
Do you see the plan of the father there?

188
00:08:50.100 --> 00:08:52.020
A few years ago I traveled up to Scotland

189
00:08:52.020 --> 00:08:53.660
to visit some friends of mine.

190
00:08:53.660 --> 00:08:55.460
There's a couple called Mark and Jill

191
00:08:55.460 --> 00:08:57.540
and there's many fascinating things

192
00:08:57.540 --> 00:08:58.900
about this wonderful couple.

193
00:08:59.300 --> 00:09:02.020
One of the sort of fascinating facts about them

194
00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:04.500
is Jill is an author, she's a published author,

195
00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:06.340
she's a great writer.

196
00:09:06.340 --> 00:09:08.040
And so one of the things that I asked them

197
00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:09.940
while I was up there with them,

198
00:09:09.940 --> 00:09:12.620
I said, Jill, what is your creative process?

199
00:09:12.620 --> 00:09:14.220
Like what does that look like?

200
00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:16.980
So when you're writing a book,

201
00:09:16.980 --> 00:09:19.860
do you kind of start on the journey

202
00:09:19.860 --> 00:09:21.700
and like you don't know where it's gonna go

203
00:09:21.700 --> 00:09:24.220
and you kind of develop it over time?

204
00:09:24.220 --> 00:09:28.000
Or do you sort of plan it all out in advance?

205
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.360
And by the look on her face,

206
00:09:29.360 --> 00:09:31.040
you could tell that I asked the right question.

207
00:09:31.040 --> 00:09:33.280
Like she was ready, she was waiting on somebody

208
00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:34.280
to finally ask.

209
00:09:34.280 --> 00:09:36.360
And she said, hold on just a second.

210
00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:38.280
And she went from the living room

211
00:09:38.280 --> 00:09:39.760
back into like a back bedroom

212
00:09:39.760 --> 00:09:42.040
and she came back out with the biggest piece of paper

213
00:09:42.040 --> 00:09:43.560
I've ever seen in my life.

214
00:09:43.560 --> 00:09:45.040
And it was all folded up.

215
00:09:45.040 --> 00:09:46.480
And she took this piece of paper

216
00:09:46.480 --> 00:09:48.560
and then she then unfolded this paper.

217
00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:51.360
And as she unfolded the paper, you could see on it,

218
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:54.760
there was all the characters listed out of her next book.

219
00:09:54.760 --> 00:09:57.200
You could see the title of her next book there.

220
00:09:57.200 --> 00:09:58.800
You could see the kind of the plot

221
00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:00.800
and the chapters kind of all mapped out

222
00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:02.840
and then how it was gonna resolve at the end

223
00:10:02.840 --> 00:10:04.400
all there on this piece of paper

224
00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:06.720
that she unfolded before me.

225
00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:08.600
It was all mapped out.

226
00:10:08.600 --> 00:10:09.720
And so what we see here,

227
00:10:09.720 --> 00:10:11.920
we have this kind of mystery

228
00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:13.040
that was there in redemption,

229
00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:14.960
but now it is unfolded before us.

230
00:10:14.960 --> 00:10:18.600
We have God's unfolding plan of redemption.

231
00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:20.880
He's not kind of making it up as he goes

232
00:10:20.880 --> 00:10:25.200
or kind of responding to things as it plays out.

233
00:10:25.240 --> 00:10:27.920
Our lives exist as part of a story

234
00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:30.640
that has been mapped out by God

235
00:10:30.640 --> 00:10:33.520
and is playing out in time.

236
00:10:33.520 --> 00:10:37.080
In Ephesians one, the author here unfolds it before our eyes

237
00:10:37.080 --> 00:10:40.920
and shows it planned from beginning to end.

238
00:10:40.920 --> 00:10:42.080
So a few things about the plan.

239
00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:45.400
One is we see the origin of the plan here.

240
00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:50.280
So verse nine, it was planned according to God's purpose.

241
00:10:50.280 --> 00:10:52.800
So the plan of redemption unfolding before us

242
00:10:52.800 --> 00:10:54.880
was determined by God's purpose

243
00:10:54.880 --> 00:10:57.680
or according to his good pleasure.

244
00:10:58.640 --> 00:11:01.040
And that includes not just the plan in general

245
00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:05.120
but also our place in that plan.

246
00:11:05.120 --> 00:11:07.320
So how does God come up with this plan?

247
00:11:07.320 --> 00:11:09.040
Well, verse 11 tells us,

248
00:11:09.040 --> 00:11:13.240
according to the counsel of his will.

249
00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:15.720
So what does that mean?

250
00:11:15.720 --> 00:11:17.440
Well, it means that God's redemption plan

251
00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:21.520
wasn't determined based on any outside influence

252
00:11:21.520 --> 00:11:23.960
beyond himself.

253
00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:26.680
It is his desires being fulfilled

254
00:11:26.680 --> 00:11:31.680
according to his all-wise and foreordained plan.

255
00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:35.960
So it was his desire that is being fulfilled in redemption.

256
00:11:37.680 --> 00:11:39.280
So you got the origin of the plan from God

257
00:11:39.280 --> 00:11:41.000
but also you see the scope of the plan here

258
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:44.280
because God is sovereign not over a lot of things

259
00:11:44.280 --> 00:11:46.840
or most things but over everything.

260
00:11:46.840 --> 00:11:51.200
And so everything is included in his redemption plan.

261
00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:53.520
His plan includes all things in heaven and on earth

262
00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:55.240
and in verse 10 he works.

263
00:11:55.240 --> 00:11:57.240
How many things according to the counsel of his will?

264
00:11:57.240 --> 00:11:59.280
Verse 11, all things.

265
00:11:59.280 --> 00:12:04.200
Nothing is outside of the scope of his sovereignty.

266
00:12:05.120 --> 00:12:07.920
It includes all things and also all time.

267
00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:11.760
We might think of time as being something that is forever

268
00:12:11.760 --> 00:12:14.800
but that's not what is presented to us in scripture.

269
00:12:15.960 --> 00:12:20.960
God's purposes were determined before time existed

270
00:12:21.160 --> 00:12:23.960
and they are being fulfilled in time

271
00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:28.960
but there is coming a day when time will be fulfilled.

272
00:12:29.080 --> 00:12:31.600
In other words, history as we know it

273
00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:34.240
will come to a final conclusion,

274
00:12:34.240 --> 00:12:39.240
a conclusion, a resolution that was determined by God.

275
00:12:39.240 --> 00:12:42.160
So the story is planned out from start to finish.

276
00:12:43.080 --> 00:12:44.520
So what's the goal of this plan?

277
00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:45.360
We might ask.

278
00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:46.800
What's God aiming at here?

279
00:12:47.640 --> 00:12:51.000
You know, Richard Dawkins once described the universe

280
00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:56.000
as being a place of no design, no purpose, no evil, no good,

281
00:12:56.680 --> 00:13:00.560
nothing but blind, pitiless indifference.

282
00:13:00.560 --> 00:13:01.460
Encouraging, right?

283
00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:04.720
But that's not what we see here.

284
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:06.840
Here we see that God has designed the universe

285
00:13:06.840 --> 00:13:08.120
with a purpose in mind.

286
00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:09.480
What is the purpose?

287
00:13:09.480 --> 00:13:12.680
The goal is the praise of his glory.

288
00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:14.840
You see that repeated three times in the passage.

289
00:13:14.880 --> 00:13:16.960
Verse six, verse 12, verse 14,

290
00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:21.960
everything exists not only by him but also for him.

291
00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:25.880
So another couple of texts to throw in here too.

292
00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:29.560
Romans chapter 11 verse 36 ties these two together.

293
00:13:29.560 --> 00:13:32.560
It says for from him and through him

294
00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:37.560
and to him are all things to him be glory forever.

295
00:13:39.280 --> 00:13:41.680
Revelation chapter four verse 11,

296
00:13:42.680 --> 00:13:44.400
God is being praised.

297
00:13:44.400 --> 00:13:47.720
And it says worthy are you, our Lord and God

298
00:13:47.720 --> 00:13:51.920
to receive glory and honor and power for you created all things.

299
00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:56.040
And by your will they were existed and were created.

300
00:13:58.360 --> 00:14:00.840
So everything exists for God's glory.

301
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:02.920
In the making of the 16th century,

302
00:14:02.920 --> 00:14:04.920
you had this guy called Copernicus.

303
00:14:04.920 --> 00:14:07.280
Remember what he proposed?

304
00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:09.880
He proposed this crazy idea

305
00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:12.960
that the earth revolved around the sun.

306
00:14:12.960 --> 00:14:14.960
And it wasn't that it wasn't the other way around

307
00:14:14.960 --> 00:14:17.000
because people believe that everything revolved

308
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:18.840
around the earth.

309
00:14:18.840 --> 00:14:21.400
It was a really controversial idea at the time

310
00:14:21.400 --> 00:14:22.720
that the earth revolved around the sun.

311
00:14:22.720 --> 00:14:25.520
It was hard for people to believe

312
00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:27.560
but nevertheless it was true.

313
00:14:27.560 --> 00:14:29.320
It may be a more controversial thing

314
00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:30.800
to say that the glory of God

315
00:14:30.800 --> 00:14:35.160
is the center of all existence but it is truth.

316
00:14:36.200 --> 00:14:39.560
You know and although we wouldn't say this out loud maybe

317
00:14:39.600 --> 00:14:42.800
we tend to think and live as though everything

318
00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:45.960
revolves around us sometimes.

319
00:14:45.960 --> 00:14:48.160
You know we want things to be according to the counsel

320
00:14:48.160 --> 00:14:49.240
of our will.

321
00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:54.240
We have our desires and we live to fulfill those desires.

322
00:14:55.440 --> 00:14:58.320
We may conceptualize of life

323
00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:00.200
as ourselves as being at the center.

324
00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:03.320
Like I'm at the center and around me are kind of

325
00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:07.560
my desires, my plans, my career, my money,

326
00:15:07.560 --> 00:15:11.440
my friends, my family, and maybe even my faith.

327
00:15:11.440 --> 00:15:13.360
And God is out there on the periphery.

328
00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:17.000
And if all that feels overwhelming or out of sorts

329
00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.200
it's because we weren't designed in that way.

330
00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:23.080
We're not here to do our will but to do God's will.

331
00:15:23.080 --> 00:15:24.640
We're not here to make much of ourselves.

332
00:15:24.640 --> 00:15:26.680
We're here to make much of him.

333
00:15:26.680 --> 00:15:28.100
He is not part of our story.

334
00:15:28.100 --> 00:15:30.960
We are part of his.

335
00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:32.400
We were created for a purpose

336
00:15:32.400 --> 00:15:35.360
and that purpose is the praise of his glory.

337
00:15:35.360 --> 00:15:37.040
And if that doesn't feel like good news

338
00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:39.240
notice how God wants to be glorified in us.

339
00:15:39.240 --> 00:15:43.440
His plan is to be glorified by pouring out his grace

340
00:15:43.440 --> 00:15:45.640
on our lives.

341
00:15:45.640 --> 00:15:46.800
So here in Ephesians one,

342
00:15:46.800 --> 00:15:49.320
God isn't being glorified just in a general sense.

343
00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:53.220
He's being glorified for his grace.

344
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:57.640
So verse six speaks of the praise of his glorious grace.

345
00:15:57.640 --> 00:16:01.120
Verse seven speaks of the riches of his grace.

346
00:16:01.120 --> 00:16:03.400
And in verse 14 he wraps things up

347
00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:05.960
by talking about God being glorified

348
00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:10.040
in giving us an inheritance.

349
00:16:10.040 --> 00:16:11.680
So yes, God created everything

350
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:13.800
with the goal of his glory in mind

351
00:16:13.800 --> 00:16:16.800
but there's a particular glory that he wanted to receive.

352
00:16:16.800 --> 00:16:20.440
And that was to be glorified for the grace

353
00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:24.560
that he has shown to the people he has redeemed.

354
00:16:25.480 --> 00:16:29.440
So God's unflinching commitment to his glory

355
00:16:29.440 --> 00:16:33.040
brings about our everlasting good.

356
00:16:33.080 --> 00:16:35.240
He displays his glory in this way

357
00:16:35.240 --> 00:16:38.080
by setting his love upon us,

358
00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:40.120
by adopting us into his family,

359
00:16:40.120 --> 00:16:42.200
by redeeming us from slavery to sin

360
00:16:42.200 --> 00:16:45.360
and by bringing us into the eternal inheritance

361
00:16:45.360 --> 00:16:49.080
he has prepared for us.

362
00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:51.600
So we were made for something infinitely greater

363
00:16:51.600 --> 00:16:55.840
than relying on ourselves to fulfill our will.

364
00:16:55.840 --> 00:17:00.360
We were made to live by God's grace for his glory.

365
00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:01.660
This is the Father's plan.

366
00:17:03.480 --> 00:17:06.040
But it doesn't just make plans, he fulfills them.

367
00:17:06.040 --> 00:17:07.880
He fulfills all of them.

368
00:17:07.880 --> 00:17:10.840
Isaiah chapter 46 verses nine and 10,

369
00:17:10.840 --> 00:17:11.920
God says this, he says,

370
00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:14.400
I am God and there is no other.

371
00:17:14.400 --> 00:17:16.560
I am God and there is no one like me

372
00:17:16.560 --> 00:17:20.080
declaring the end from the beginning.

373
00:17:20.080 --> 00:17:23.120
And from ancient times things not yet done

374
00:17:23.120 --> 00:17:26.600
saying my counsel shall stand

375
00:17:26.600 --> 00:17:30.860
and I will accomplish all of my purpose.

376
00:17:30.900 --> 00:17:34.660
So God accomplishes all that he plans.

377
00:17:34.660 --> 00:17:37.960
So how was his redemption plan accomplished?

378
00:17:39.100 --> 00:17:41.020
Let's move this into the second thing.

379
00:17:41.020 --> 00:17:43.540
It is accomplished by the Son.

380
00:17:44.740 --> 00:17:47.700
So the Father's redemptive plan is accomplished

381
00:17:47.700 --> 00:17:50.860
through the redemptive work of the Son.

382
00:17:50.860 --> 00:17:53.780
It's accomplished by Jesus when he came into this world.

383
00:17:53.780 --> 00:17:56.300
His plan in verse nine, there at the end of the verse

384
00:17:56.300 --> 00:17:58.980
is set forth in Christ.

385
00:17:58.980 --> 00:18:01.340
And that word set forth means to lay before.

386
00:18:01.340 --> 00:18:02.740
You might think of like, I don't know,

387
00:18:02.740 --> 00:18:05.420
an architect laying out a blueprint.

388
00:18:05.420 --> 00:18:06.940
He sets it before him.

389
00:18:06.940 --> 00:18:09.100
So he set out this redemptive plan

390
00:18:09.100 --> 00:18:11.700
that he is going to accomplish in Christ.

391
00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:13.320
It is before him.

392
00:18:13.320 --> 00:18:16.060
That's what God was looking at in eternity.

393
00:18:16.060 --> 00:18:18.820
And then when he pours out his grace on our lives

394
00:18:18.820 --> 00:18:22.580
he pours it out on us in Christ.

395
00:18:22.580 --> 00:18:25.540
He pours it out on those who are united to Christ.

396
00:18:25.540 --> 00:18:27.580
So we've seen it right the way through.

397
00:18:27.620 --> 00:18:30.260
Chosen, yes, but chosen in him.

398
00:18:30.260 --> 00:18:32.940
We are adopted, yes, but we are adopted

399
00:18:32.940 --> 00:18:34.900
through Jesus Christ.

400
00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:36.700
We are redeemed, set free from sin,

401
00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:41.700
how through his blood he paid the price for our sin.

402
00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:45.260
We have been given an eternal inheritance.

403
00:18:45.260 --> 00:18:46.100
Where?

404
00:18:46.100 --> 00:18:48.900
Verse 11, in him.

405
00:18:52.980 --> 00:18:54.620
So it's in Christ that all the blessings

406
00:18:54.620 --> 00:18:56.500
of God are received.

407
00:18:58.140 --> 00:19:00.060
One of my favorite places to go as a kid

408
00:19:00.060 --> 00:19:01.620
was Six Flags over Georgia.

409
00:19:01.620 --> 00:19:02.860
You haven't been there?

410
00:19:02.860 --> 00:19:05.740
And I remember going to,

411
00:19:05.740 --> 00:19:08.380
we'd go in the summertime and it'd be really, really hot

412
00:19:08.380 --> 00:19:12.140
and you'd just be wanting to cool down somehow,

413
00:19:12.140 --> 00:19:15.100
but I remember finding the perfect place to cool down.

414
00:19:15.100 --> 00:19:18.140
And there was a ride aptly called Splashwater Falls.

415
00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:20.540
I think it's been discontinued.

416
00:19:20.540 --> 00:19:23.100
The Splashwater Falls, it takes you up in this boat

417
00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:25.220
all the way to the top of this kind of waterfall

418
00:19:25.220 --> 00:19:27.820
and it drops you down and as it gets down to the bottom,

419
00:19:27.820 --> 00:19:30.740
there's just this huge splash that's there.

420
00:19:30.740 --> 00:19:35.100
And the best place to get the refreshment of that splash

421
00:19:35.100 --> 00:19:36.900
was not on the boat.

422
00:19:36.900 --> 00:19:38.380
It was on the bridge, yes.

423
00:19:38.380 --> 00:19:40.500
There was a little bridge that went across

424
00:19:40.500 --> 00:19:44.060
and you just knew that the place to get that

425
00:19:44.060 --> 00:19:46.880
was on that bridge and it was amazing.

426
00:19:48.180 --> 00:19:49.260
You could think of, I don't know,

427
00:19:49.260 --> 00:19:51.580
this passage is that kind of tidal wave of blessing.

428
00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:54.620
Like it's really coming on thick here.

429
00:19:54.660 --> 00:19:56.820
All these blessings that we have been given

430
00:19:56.820 --> 00:20:00.020
and there's a place that we can know that we are loved by God,

431
00:20:00.020 --> 00:20:02.580
that we are His children, that we're set free from our sins,

432
00:20:02.580 --> 00:20:04.220
that we have an eternal hope.

433
00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:06.100
Where is that place where we can receive

434
00:20:06.100 --> 00:20:08.420
all of these things where this tidal wave of blessing

435
00:20:08.420 --> 00:20:09.460
comes over us?

436
00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:11.540
It is in Christ.

437
00:20:12.640 --> 00:20:14.300
It's through faith in Him, if you will,

438
00:20:14.300 --> 00:20:16.600
that we step on to that bridge.

439
00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:20.280
He is the bridge in that sense.

440
00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:23.700
So we receive those blessings, verse 13,

441
00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:25.540
when we believe in Christ.

442
00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:26.980
That's how we can know we are in Him,

443
00:20:26.980 --> 00:20:28.700
if our faith is in Him.

444
00:20:29.940 --> 00:20:33.260
I wanna draw your attention to a couple of things

445
00:20:33.260 --> 00:20:34.980
this week in verses nine and 10,

446
00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:37.060
that sort of draws into the bigger picture

447
00:20:37.060 --> 00:20:39.660
of what Christ accomplished when He came into the world.

448
00:20:39.660 --> 00:20:42.500
We focused on those individual blessings last week,

449
00:20:42.500 --> 00:20:44.420
but remember, these two verses encapsulate

450
00:20:44.420 --> 00:20:45.860
what the whole book is about.

451
00:20:46.820 --> 00:20:50.300
So, what is the plan that God sets forth in Christ

452
00:20:50.300 --> 00:20:52.020
for the fullness of time?

453
00:20:52.020 --> 00:20:53.020
Here it is.

454
00:20:53.020 --> 00:20:58.020
To unite all things in Him in heaven and on earth.

455
00:20:58.300 --> 00:21:00.780
So what's the plan that He accomplished?

456
00:21:00.780 --> 00:21:04.380
The plan to unite all things in Him.

457
00:21:05.820 --> 00:21:07.540
What does that mean?

458
00:21:07.540 --> 00:21:08.700
What's He talking about here?

459
00:21:08.700 --> 00:21:11.340
Well, the word unite means to sum up

460
00:21:11.340 --> 00:21:14.460
or to draw together into one.

461
00:21:14.460 --> 00:21:15.820
If it's helpful, maybe you can think of,

462
00:21:15.820 --> 00:21:18.020
I don't know, like the Amazon River.

463
00:21:18.020 --> 00:21:21.140
So you got 1,100 tributaries

464
00:21:21.140 --> 00:21:23.140
that all make up this one river.

465
00:21:23.140 --> 00:21:25.500
They're all flowing into this singular river

466
00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:29.180
and all them being brought to the same end.

467
00:21:29.180 --> 00:21:31.660
So all of history and all of creation

468
00:21:31.660 --> 00:21:34.980
is moving towards the goal for which it was created

469
00:21:34.980 --> 00:21:36.780
and what draws it all together

470
00:21:36.780 --> 00:21:38.740
and brings it to that end?

471
00:21:39.980 --> 00:21:42.100
It's Christ and what He accomplished

472
00:21:42.100 --> 00:21:46.300
through His life and death and resurrection and ascension.

473
00:21:47.140 --> 00:21:51.120
So God's plan of redemption doesn't just include us.

474
00:21:51.120 --> 00:21:56.120
It includes all of creation, the whole spectrum of creation.

475
00:21:58.920 --> 00:22:00.840
So to give you another verse, Romans chapter eight

476
00:22:00.840 --> 00:22:05.840
and verse 21 says, creation itself will be set free

477
00:22:06.840 --> 00:22:09.120
from its bondage to corruption

478
00:22:09.120 --> 00:22:11.520
and obtain the freedom of the glory

479
00:22:11.520 --> 00:22:13.880
of the children of God.

480
00:22:13.880 --> 00:22:16.040
Did Jesus come to set us free?

481
00:22:16.040 --> 00:22:19.040
Absolutely, but not only us, not just redeem us

482
00:22:19.080 --> 00:22:21.200
but the whole spectrum of creation.

483
00:22:21.200 --> 00:22:22.760
So when we look at the world around us,

484
00:22:22.760 --> 00:22:26.960
we might look and see, this is a world of suffering

485
00:22:26.960 --> 00:22:29.720
and we might start to think, well, maybe this is a universe

486
00:22:29.720 --> 00:22:32.760
of blind, pitiless indifference,

487
00:22:34.080 --> 00:22:37.920
but there is coming a day when everything will be made right,

488
00:22:37.920 --> 00:22:40.160
when all things will be made new,

489
00:22:40.160 --> 00:22:43.200
when everything will be brought into alignment

490
00:22:43.200 --> 00:22:45.960
with God's good purposes.

491
00:22:45.960 --> 00:22:47.960
And on that day, all of creation

492
00:22:48.000 --> 00:22:51.480
will reflect his goodness and his beauty.

493
00:22:52.680 --> 00:22:55.080
So Jesus' reign and his redemptive work

494
00:22:55.080 --> 00:22:58.160
will be fully realized at the end of time.

495
00:23:01.200 --> 00:23:04.960
When he comes again, there will be a new creation

496
00:23:04.960 --> 00:23:08.000
and we will there dwell with him forever.

497
00:23:08.000 --> 00:23:09.960
And there everything will be united,

498
00:23:09.960 --> 00:23:12.400
drawn together under his reign.

499
00:23:14.240 --> 00:23:15.960
But there is a place where his reign

500
00:23:15.960 --> 00:23:18.680
and the unity that that brings can be seen now

501
00:23:18.680 --> 00:23:21.400
and that is in the unity of the church.

502
00:23:22.600 --> 00:23:25.040
Now the church is to be a microcosm

503
00:23:25.040 --> 00:23:28.740
for what he has planned for the whole of creation.

504
00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:31.800
So Paul goes on to talk about those

505
00:23:31.800 --> 00:23:34.320
who are heading towards that inheritance,

506
00:23:34.320 --> 00:23:36.560
like that perfect new creation that we will step into

507
00:23:36.560 --> 00:23:38.520
where all the whole spectrum of creation

508
00:23:38.520 --> 00:23:39.940
is united in Christ.

509
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:43.200
Who's heading for that inheritance?

510
00:23:43.200 --> 00:23:46.240
Well, there are two groups of people that he mentions

511
00:23:46.240 --> 00:23:49.080
and then he mentions about how God has united them together

512
00:23:49.080 --> 00:23:51.080
and you see that throughout the rest of Ephesians.

513
00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:52.200
But who are these two groups of people?

514
00:23:52.200 --> 00:23:55.440
One, those who were the first to hope in Christ,

515
00:23:55.440 --> 00:23:58.440
in verse 12, he includes himself in that number.

516
00:23:58.440 --> 00:24:02.480
And he talks about others who hear and believe

517
00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:03.760
the gospel.

518
00:24:03.760 --> 00:24:06.200
So what's going on here when he's saying

519
00:24:06.200 --> 00:24:09.440
the people moving towards that perfect end

520
00:24:09.440 --> 00:24:11.600
are those who were the first to hope in Christ

521
00:24:11.640 --> 00:24:13.920
and everyone who believes the gospel.

522
00:24:13.920 --> 00:24:16.200
Who were the first to hope in Christ?

523
00:24:16.200 --> 00:24:19.120
They were Jews who had put their faith in God

524
00:24:19.120 --> 00:24:23.680
and put their trust in Jesus as their Messiah and King.

525
00:24:23.680 --> 00:24:26.760
And it's interesting when you read this passage

526
00:24:26.760 --> 00:24:28.600
in light of the Old Testament scriptures,

527
